t-login`, `but-sync`, `but-cloud`, and `but-takeover` binaries.\n\nConfiguration:\n\n```env\nDATABASE_HOST=\"aws.connect.psdb.cloud/gitbutler_dev\"\nDATABASE_USERNAME=\"<planetscale username>\"\nDATABASE_PASSWORD=\"<planetscale password>\"\nSESSION_SECRET=\"<random 32+ bytes>\"\nPIERRE_ORG_NAME=\"your-org\"\nPIERRE_PRIVATE_KEY=\"<PKCS8 PEM>\"\nBOWTIE_PUBLIC_BASE_URL=\"http://localhost:3000\"\n```\n\nThe private key \n[TRUNCATED]\n\nProduction environment:\n\n1. Deploy the Next.js app with `BOWTIE_PUBLIC_BASE_URL=\"https://gitbutler.dev\"`.\n2. Create a PlanetScale production branch password for the app.\n3. Store `DATABASE_HOST`, `DATABASE_USERNAME`, and `DATABASE_PASSWORD` only in\n   the deployment secret store.\n4. Apply schema changes to PlanetScale through its deploy-request workflow, not\n   ad hoc production `db push`.\n5. Keep `SESSION_SECRET`, `PIERRE_ORG_NAME`, `PIERRE_PRIVATE_KEY`, and database\n   credentials in deployment secrets.\n\nThe Drizzle schema lives in `db/schema.ts`; `drizzle-kit push` applies schema\nupdates to the PlanetScale branch selected by the current environment.\n\n## Server Interfaces\n\nBrowser auth:\n\n[REDACTED:entropy] `POST /api/auth/signup`\n- `POST /api/auth/login`\n- `POST /api/auth/logout`\n- `/signup?next=...` and `/login?next=...` redirect back to device approval.\n\nCLI device auth:\n\n[REDACTED:entropy] `POST /api/cli/device/start`\n  - Body: `{ clientId, clientNickname? }`\n  - Returns `{ deviceCode, userCode, authUrl, expiresAt, pollIntervalSeconds }`\n- `GET /cli/device/[userCode]`\n  - Shows login/signup links or an approval form for the signed-in user.\n- `POST /api/cli/device/approve`\n  - Binds the device login to the browser user.\n- `GET /api/cli/device/poll?deviceCode=...`\n  - Returns `pending`, `expired`, `consumed`, or an approved cloud token.\n\nCloud project APIs:\n\n- `POST /api/cloud/projects/resolve`\n  - Bearer-authenticated with a cloud token.\n  - Body: `{ projectId?, canonicalRemoteUrl?, localName?, initialRemoteUrl?, clientId, clientNickname? }`\n  - Finds or creates a `CloudProject`, provisions the backing code.storage repo,\n    and returns the cloud Git URL plus push/fetch refspecs.\n- `GET /api/cloud/clients`\n  - Lists approved CLI clients for the signed-in browser user.\n- `DELETE /api/cloud/clients/[id]`\n  - Revokes active tokens for that client.\n\nGit proxy:\n\n- Public cloud Git URL: `/cloud/<project_id>.git`\n- Middleware rewrites Smart HTTP paths to:\n  - `/api/cloud/git/[project]/info/refs`\n  - `/api/cloud/git/[project]/git-upload-pack`\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-24T15:08:24.560Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}